‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Who are Kara and Nate?! 

2016-2019: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FuFv4iF8wgg&t=1s  

2020-2024: https://youtu.be/ikAN9e0gBaU?si=G644UGWIqPrOzTYW 

Originally from Nashville, Tennessee, we got married 2013 and were super ‚Äúnormal.‚Äù I was a teacher and Nate started a small printing business from the spare bedroom of our apartment. 

We discovered the world of ‚Äútravel hacking‚Äù while planning our honeymoon & became addicted ;)

So after 2 years of obsessively saving $35k and over 2 million miles and points, we sold our cars and apartment and left home January 10, 2016 for a ‚Äúone year‚Äù trip around the world.

Our goal was to see as many places as possible before we ran out of money and went back home to ‚Äúnormal life.‚Äù We started this channel to share our experiences with friends and family, but quickly fell in love with living on the road and found a new passion for capturing our travels through video. So we did everything we could to keep going.

4 years later, we achieved our new goal of visiting 100 countries and all 7 continents. We had no plans to slow down, until 2020 forced us to ;) Which is when we bought a converted van to start exploring our own country for the first time!

After ~2 years of van life, we are back to full time international traveling! And now we are in our 10TH YEAR of finding the best adventures the world has to offer :) 

We are incredibly grateful to be able to continue doing something we love every day. üòäüé•üåé Thank you to everyone who has been a part of our journey!

title: 3 Beautiful Swiss Villages That Left Me Speechless (Switzerland‚Äôs Heaven!)
description:
Three amazing Swiss locations in one peaceful walking tour: Sonogno, Grindelwald and Lauterbrunnen.
Join me for a slow journey through some of the most beautiful corners of Switzerland ‚Äì from a hidden Ticino village at the end of a valley to the famous alpine resorts of the Bernese Oberland.

‚ùóImportant - turn on subtitles in your native language in the settings - "CC"
üì∫ For the best viewing experience, watch on a smart TV or a bigger screen instead of your phone.

üìå Locations: Sonogno ‚Ä¢ Grindelwald ‚Ä¢ Lauterbrunnen ‚Ä¢ (Switzerland)
Date recorded: June ‚õÖWeather: 24¬∞C/ 75¬∞F

üèî Sonogno ‚Äì End of the Verzasca Valley
Our journey begins in Sonogno, one of the most remote and picturesque villages in Switzerland. Tucked away at the very end of the Verzasca Valley, in Italian-speaking Ticino, Sonogno feels like a place where time has stopped. Its traditional stone houses with flower-filled balconies, narrow cobbled lanes, and the sound of mountain streams create an atmosphere that is pure peace.

Just a short, easy walk from the village you‚Äôll find Cascata La Froda, a beautiful waterfall hidden at the foot of the mountains. It‚Äôs an incredibly serene spot, with fresh air, moss-covered rocks, and birdsong all around. Few travelers make it here, so it feels like your own secret discovery.

This valley is also famous for its handmade wool crafts ‚Äì the village has a small Casa della Lana (House of Wool), where you can see weaving demonstrations and buy traditional products. Stop in one of the rustic grotto restaurants to try Ticino specialties like polenta, local cheeses, chestnut desserts, or honey made right in the valley.

üèû Grindelwald ‚Äì The Village Beneath the Eiger
From Ticino we travel north into the heart of the Bernese Alps to Grindelwald, one of the most famous villages in Switzerland. Surrounded by dramatic peaks, with the legendary Eiger North Face towering above, Grindelwald is a dream for mountain lovers. Wooden chalets, flowered balconies, and incredible views in every direction ‚Äì it‚Äôs a place that looks like it stepped out of a postcard.

Grindelwald is known for its scenic trails and mountain activities. You can take the gondola to First Cliff Walk, an adrenaline-filled walkway suspended above the valley, or ride the train up to Jungfraujoch, the highest railway station in Europe at 3454 m, with views of the Aletsch Glacier and the famous Ice Palace carved deep into the glacier itself.

Even if you just stroll through the village, the combination of cowbells, green pastures, and those enormous mountain walls is unforgettable.

üåü Lauterbrunnen ‚Äì The Valley of 72 Waterfalls 
We end this long walking journey in Lauterbrunnen, one of the most spectacular valleys in the world. Steep cliffs rise almost vertically on both sides, and waterfalls pour down everywhere you look ‚Äì there are said to be 72 of them! The Staubbach Falls, dropping almost 300 m beside the village, inspired poets like Goethe.

Inside the mountain, the Tr√ºmmelbach Falls thunder through narrow rock tunnels ‚Äì ten glacier-fed waterfalls hidden in the dark, an experience that you can feel with all your senses.

The valley is also a base for exploring car-free alpine villages like M√ºrren and Wengen, reachable only by cable car or train. And for thrill-seekers, Lauterbrunnen is the base-jumping capital of Europe. But even if you‚Äôre here just to walk, the atmosphere ‚Äì the sound of waterfalls, the scent of alpine meadows, the echo of cowbells ‚Äì feels like nowhere else on Earth.

ü•æ Why watch this?
If you love Switzerland, walking tours, 4K slow travel, mountain scenery, waterfalls, and peaceful alpine villages, this long video lets you experience three incredible places in one journey.
Take a deep breath, slow down, and enjoy the magic of Sonogno, Grindelwald and Lauterbrunnen.

üëâ Don‚Äôt forget to like, subscribe, and hit the bell for more amazing travel videos! üöÄ
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCM6bqa9BISRwXde7XJER11Q?sub_confirmation=1

Feel free to share your thoughts in the comments! I would be thrilled to hear your opinion and questions. Thank you for watching!‚ù§Ô∏è

title: New York Trip | The BEST of New York Food | New York Neighborhoods | New York Travel Vlog
description:
Join Bilal and Shaeeda from 90 Day Fianc√©, Happily Ever After?, and 90 Day Fianc√©: Pillow Talk as they take you on a fun-filled travel adventure to the city that never sleeps ‚Äî New York City! üá∫üá∏‚ú®

This trip is extra special because it‚Äôs not just Bilal and Shaeeda this time ‚Äî they‚Äôre bringing along their adorable 10-month-old son, baby Ayaan, for his very first New York experience! From the hustle and bustle of Times Square to the peaceful strolls through Central Park, this vlog captures every laugh, challenge, and heartwarming family moment as they explore the Big Apple together. ‚ù§Ô∏è

Although Bilal and Shaeeda have been to New York many times before, traveling with a baby changes everything. Will the busy subways, noisy streets, and crowded attractions be too much for little Ayaan ‚Äî or will he fall in love with the energy of the city just like his parents? Watch as the couple navigates parenthood on the go, proving that love, laughter, and patience are the real travel essentials.

In this episode, you‚Äôll see the family:
üöÜ Ride through the New York subway like true locals.
üåá Explore iconic neighborhoods such as Brooklyn and Manhattan.
üå≥ Enjoy quiet moments in parks amid the chaos of city life.
üçΩÔ∏è Taste some of New York‚Äôs best food, including a special stop where Shaeeda gets a taste of home ‚Äî Trinidad and Tobago cuisine right in the heart of NYC!

Whether it‚Äôs taking in the skyline views, trying new foods, or managing stroller life in crowded streets, Bilal and Shaeeda keep things real and relatable. You‚Äôll laugh, learn, and maybe even get inspired to plan your own family trip to New York!

So grab your popcorn (or doubles üòâ), sit back, and join us for an unforgettable ride through New York City with Bilal, Shaeeda, and baby Ayaan. Don‚Äôt forget to like, comment, and subscribe ‚Äî and tell us in the comments what part of New York we should visit next!

Our Ultimate Travel Guide to Bangkok, Thailand! We're back in Bangkok this summer to explore all the best things to see and places to visit in the Thai capital.

Planning a trip to Bangkok? Check out our 3 Day Bangkok Travel Itinerary:

Day 1: After an Eastern Thai dinner and checking into our hotel, we spend our first morning exploring the best cafes in Bangkok's Ekkamai district. Then we revisit our favorite Thai food spots in Bangkok, starting at one of the best restaurants in Central Embassy. The rest of the afternoon is for shopping and Thai massages before dinner at a Michelin Guide favorite, Polo Fried Chicken.

Day 2:
More Cafe hopping before spending the day at one Bangkok's most popular shopping malls, Icon Siam. Its Souk Food Court is a must-visit for Thai street food. Lunch is at a legendary Pad Thai restuarant and dinner is at a Michelin Northern Thai restaurant.

Day 3:
After having the best brunch in Bangkok and checking out a must-try Thai cafe, we explore more of Bangkok's best luxury malls, have dinner at a Michelin Chicken Rice shop, and even pass by a festival honoring the country's unique Thai fruits.

Join us next week for more of our Thailand Travels!

Shot in May 2025

description:
My 1st Arrival In New York City, USA - First impressions of New York City, USA 
Grab a Holafly eSIM for your next trip and use discount code KENABROAD at checkout ‚Äì or just click the link https://holafly.sjv.io/yqBmNN 

I have finally arrived in New York City, USA. It's my first time in New York and in this USA travel vlog I share my first arrival impressions in New York. You can follow the journey from the airport into Manhattan to see my first impressions of New York. From navigating the New York trains to a classic yellow cab ride, I show what arriving in New York really looks like for a tourist in New York.

We stop for an American breakfast diner experience before walking past landmarks like the Empire State Building and heading into Times Square for those iconic lights. At the Times Square I check into my hotel and keep filming my first impressions, comparing expectations with reality in the biggest city in the USA. If you plan to travel to New York City too, this New York vlog will give you good impressions of what it's like to arrive in New York for the first time. 

I am going to stay in the United States for a few weeks and travel the USA a bit, so if you're new here and would like to follow my USA trip feel free to subscribe. Have you ever been to New York City? What were your first impressions of the USA or of New York? Let me know in the comments.

title: Kerala Trip Vlog | Houseboat, Varkala & Kochi Adventures
description:
Embark on an unforgettable Kerala trip in this India vlog as we journey from the bustling capital of Trivandrum to the tranquil cliffs of Varkala, glide through the serene Kerala backwaters on a traditional Kerala houseboat, and dive into the rich culture of Kochi. Along the way, we explore India‚Äôs largest mall, witness spiritual rituals on the beach, visit ancient temples and historic forts, and experience the magic of a live Kathakali dance performance. 

From coastal sunsets and yoga by the Arabian Sea to tasting mouthwatering seafood and jamming with locals in Fort Kochi, this Kerala travel adventure is packed with breathtaking scenery, history, spirituality, and unforgettable cultural moments. Whether you‚Äôre planning your own Kerala trip or simply dreaming of India, this travel vlog will transport you straight into the heart of God‚Äôs Own Country.

#KeralaTrip #IndiaVlog #KeralaHouseboat #KeralaBackwaters #Trivandrum #Varkala #Alleppey #Kochi #FortKochi #Kathakali #KeralaTravelVlog #TravelIndia #KeralaTourism #VisitKerala #KeralaBeach #SouthIndiaTravel #IndianFood #KeralaCulture #KeralaAdventure #TravelVlogIndia

Subscribe to Global Travel Stories https://www.youtube.com/c/GlobalTravelStories and join the adventures around the globe! If you are enjoying this video/series please share us with friends and family on social media.

Tours used in this video:

Intrepid Travel: Iconic India
https://www.intrepidtravel.com/nz/india/iconic-india-144634

Kochi Kathakali Show:
https://www.keralakathakali.com/

Chapters:

Introduction 0:00

Trivandrum 1:04

Explore Trivandrum's Ultra-Modern Lulu Mall & Cultural Harmony
Starting our Kerala Trip we landed bright and early in Thiruvananthapuram (Trivandrum) and had a few hours to spare‚Äîso we dove straight into the colossal Lulu Mall, the largest in India and second largest in Asia! From bustling open markets and a mini theme-park complete with a roller coaster, to a jaw-dropping food court with seating for 2,500, it was overloaded with excitement (and delicious eats). As evening approached, we drifted through the vibrant local produce and fish markets, pausing to soak in an illuminated temple, mosque, and church‚Äîstanding side by side in a beautiful testament to religious harmony.

Varkala 5:30

Mystical Varkala Cliffs & Sacred Morning Rituals on the Beach
Our journey from Trivandrum led us to Varkala‚Äîa coastal gem framed by dramatic cliffs and the Arabian Sea. We stopped at the historic Anjengo Fort, among the earliest British-built forts in India (1699), before arriving at Varkala‚Äôs stunning cliff-lined shoreline. The day wound down with monsoon waves crashing against golden sand, offering a breathtaking coastal finale.
The next morning, we rose early to witness serene rituals unfolding at Papanasam Beach, followed by spiritual calm inside the ancient Sri Janardhana Temple (a historic Vishnu shrine). Midday brought yoga and a refreshing swim at Black Beach. A sudden rainstorm chased us back‚Äîbut cleared just in time for a cliff-top seafood dinner under clearing skies.

Alleppey Kerala Backwaters 16:25

Soothing Houseboat Journey Through Kerala‚Äôs Backwaters
After a scenic train ride to Alleppey, we boarded a traditional rice barge kerala houseboat and glided through the tranquil backwaters. Surrounded by lush coconut groves and colorful kingfishers, we witnessed locals paddling traditional canoes and rice paddies shimmering like emeralds. Later, we settled into a charming homestay on a peaceful island‚Äîwhere we explored rich flora, birdlife, and local rice farming. It felt like stepping into a serene green paradise.

Kochi Kathakali 31:11

Cultural Immersion: Fort Kochi & a Mesmerizing Kathakali Show
After drifting through the backwaters passing our  Kerala Houseboat, we took a local bus to Kochi‚Äôs historic Fort Kochi. The streets unfolded centuries of colonial history‚ÄîPortuguese in the 1500s, followed by Dutch and British influences. As dusk fell, we were spellbound by a live Kathakali performance: intricate gestures, expressive storytelling, and vibrant costumes created a mesmerising sensory tapestry we‚Äôll never forget.

Historic Kochi Tour 44:59

Sunrise Strolls, Colonial Relics & Coastal Culinary Delights in Kochi
We began at sunrise in Fort Kochi‚Äîcool air and quiet streets set the tone for an immersive historical walk. We visited St. Francis Church, Kerala‚Äôs oldest, housing the remains of Vasco da Gama, then explored the atmospheric Jewish Quarter and its still-functioning synagogue. On the waterfront, we watched the iconic Chinese fishing nets at work‚Äîliving relics of the 13th-century spice trade. Dinner was equally enchanting: fish wrapped in banana leaf, seasoned with fresh coriander, followed by an impromptu jam session in a local music store with the owner‚Äôs musically gifted son. Check out our India Vlog!

title: Kyrgyzstan - Negara Paling EPIC untuk Kaki Outdoor & Nature Lovers!
description:

title: Learn English Through My Trip to London üá¨üáß | Comprehensible Input
description:
Learn English naturally with this travel vlog as I explore London and my hometown in York ‚Äî teaching real-life English through conversations, street scenes, and family moments (using comprehensible input).

In this video, we‚Ä¶
 1. Learn 30+ everyday English words and expressions from real life in London ‚Äî including transport, sightseeing, and family talk.
 2. Explore famous streets and quiet corners, learning natural ways to describe what you see, do, and feel in British English.
 3. Spend time with my uncle and chat casually, helping you understand real conversation rhythms and common vocabulary.

Bonus: Watch cinematic scenes of London life and get English explanations that make it easier to remember and speak fluently.

my solo trip to the swiss alps
description:
WATCH THIS VERSION INSTEAD IT'S MUCH BETTER: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t5daW6S3sPc&t=621s

i know some (most) of the song choices are a bit random, there were copyright claims to the original music (and i hastily edited with subpar music which apparently is IRREVERSABLE) :(


EDIT: wow- thank you guys for all the love on this video!! i've seen so many comments saying that this video has inspired them to visit appenzell, and i'm so excited for you all to explore this amazing place - it's truly an unforgettable experience

but please, if you do visit, LEAVE NO TRACE. increased foot traffic often leads to more litter, damaged trails, and harm to wildlife. so please, let's work together to protect these beautiful places - respect nature, stay on marked trails, pack out everything you bring in, and leave it better than you found it. that way, others can enjoy it just as much as you (and i) did :)


hiking routes:
day 1- https://www.alltrails.com/explore/trail/switzerland/outer-rhodes/ebenalp-schafler-seealpsee-wasserauen?u=i
*note: if you have sore/weak knees and want to do the day one hike- I would recommend doing it in reverse (starting at the lake and hiking up)- it's a steep decent that is not for the weak knees (literally)
day 2- https://www.alltrails.com/explore/trail/switzerland/appenzell-inner-rhodes/schwende-seealpsee?u=i

title: Best Beach in the World | Maya Bay | Thailand Travel Vlog | Phi Phi Island
description:
Best Beach in the World | Maya Bay | Thailand Travel Vlog | Phi Phi Island

This stunning location is üìçMaya Bay which is a popular tourist destination known for its beautiful beaches and clear blue waters. It is one of most amazing place and beach in entire Thailand.


Maya bay thailand how to get there?
By Long Tail Boat it takes around 30 minutes to reach Here. However you cal also take speed boat from, ferry to tour to Maya Bay and Ko Phi phi Lee from Railay West, Railay East, Ao Nang Beach, Krabi town or Phuket.

The boat tours covers:
Viking cave,
Loh Sarah Bay
Pi Leh Bay or Pi Leh Lagoon
Some beautiful snorkelling spots around the island
Maya bay
Monkey Beach
Bamboo Beach,
Ton Sai Pier
Loh Dalum Beach,
Nui Bay
Long Beach

Here are few things to know before you go to Maya Bay:
-To avoid the crowds and enjoy the natural beauty of the area, it is best to visit Maya Bay early in the morning before 9:00 AM to explore the area before the influx of tourists

- Or late in the afternoon after 3:00 PM, when most of the day-trippers have left the island.

-Swimming is prohibited in Maya Bay.

-Boats are not permitted to anchor in the bay.

-The number of visitors allowed to enter Maya Bay has been restricted.

-National Park Fees 400 Baht per adult | 200 Baht per child.

Share it with someone who is planning to visit Maya Bay during their Thailand trip üáπüá≠

title: Spend a rainy day in Paris with me #paris #travel #vlog #rain #rainyday #cozy #paristravelguide
description:
Rainy Day in Paris ‚Äì Part 2 ‚òîÔ∏è

Paris in the rain invites you to slow down ‚Äî to wander, linger, and notice things you might otherwise pass by. These are some of my favorite places to escape the drizzle and still feel the magic of the city, and all are free to visit!


üìçMus√©e des Archives Nationales ‚Äì 60 Rue des Francs Bourgeois, 3√®meThis quiet museum is housed in a grand 17th-century mansion and holds centuries of French history ‚Äî royal decrees, maps, personal letters, even Marie Antoinette‚Äôs last letter. It‚Äôs free to enter and rarely crowded, making it the perfect rainy day refuge.

üìçLes Passages Couverts ‚Äì 1er & 2√®me arrondissementsStep into the covered arcades of Paris ‚Äî Passage Vivienne, Panoramas, Verdeau, and V√©ro-Dodat. Built in the 19th century, these glass-roofed passages are lined with antique bookstores, stamp shops, tea salons, and boutiques frozen in time. Most are within walking distance of each other and you can drift from one to the next, protected from the rain.

üìçBiblioth√®que Richelieu ‚Äì 5 Rue Vivienne, 2√®meOnce the home of the National Library of France, Richelieu has been transformed into a modern research library ‚Äî but its historic reading room remains, a stunning circular space with a soaring domed ceiling and soft, filtered light. Free to visit, peaceful to sit in, and it feels like a secret.

üìç√Ä la M√®re de Famille ‚Äì 35 Rue du Faubourg Montmartre, 9√®meParis‚Äôs oldest chocolate shop, founded in 1761. Inside, everything is still wrapped in ribbons and nostalgia ‚Äî candied chestnuts, p√¢tes de fruits, glazed orange peels, and thick old-fashioned hot chocolate. It‚Äôs like stepping back in time (and smells like it too).

üìçPalais Royal ‚Äì 8 Rue de Montpensier, 1erRain makes the arcades echo and the gardens feel even more cinematic. Find shelter under the stone colonnades, watch the drops fall on the reflecting pool, and peek into the arcades‚Äô hidden shops and galleries along the garden. 

Let me know if you want a Part 3 ‚Äî there are so many more cozy corners to share.

title: VALENCIA TRAVEL VLOG | Exploring My Favorite City in Spain üá™üá∏
description:
Hello from Valencia in Spain! üá™üá∏ I spent a whole month living in Valencia and fell in love with this city! Here‚Äôs a glimpse of the things you can do and see in Valencia if you‚Äôre planning a trip here.

Valencia is a place where historic charm meets Mediterranean vibes. From wandering through the old town and trying local delicacies to relaxing at the beach and discovering hidden spots around the city and also exploring Las Fallas (in the next vlog), this was such a fun and fulfilling trip!

Visit the stunning City of Arts and Sciences, explore the charming Old Town, relax at Malvarrosa Beach, stroll through Turia Park, check out the Central Market, admire street art in El Carmen, and end your day with a sunset catamaran cruise on the Mediterranean. And don‚Äôt forget all the amazing food Valencia has to offer!

Whether you‚Äôre planning a trip to Spain or just want to escape for a few minutes, I hope this vlog gives you some travel inspiration.

title: Ooty to Kerala: Last Minute Travel Nightmare! ü§Ø (KSRTC Bus Saved Our Trip!) South Indian Vlog
description:
Our trip nearly ended in disaster! After wrapping up our time in Ooty, we rushed to Coimbatore station only to realize our train tickets were booked for the wrong month! India Travel Fail achieved! ü§Ø

With no time to waste, we made the immediate, desperate decision to switch to the iconic KSRTC bus for a grueling 12-hour journey back to Kerala (Kochi/Ernakulam).

But first, we had to refuel! We grabbed breakfast at the absolutely famous Annapoorna, sampling some of the best South Indian local food, and loaded up on regional sweets at the renowned Anandhaas for the long road ahead.

Join us for this raw, unscripted travel day‚Äîfrom the panic of realizing our mistake, to the chaos of the bus stand, the comfort of amazing Coimbatore food, and the long, scenic grind across state lines on one of India's public transport legends. The KSRTC bus truly saved our trip and gave us an authentic look at cross-state travel!

If you love travel challenges, authentic local experiences, and seeing how travelers recover from total disasters, this is the ultimate travel vlog for you!

In this India Bus Journey Vlog, you'll see:

India Travel Fail: Missing our ‚Äúbooked‚Äù train!

The KSRTC Bus experience (Our trip's hero!)

Coimbatore's most famous breakfast spot (Annapoorna)

The long, cross-state Bus Journey from Tamil Nadu to Kerala

Tasting Indian sweets on a long-haul trip from Anandhaas

Public Transport adventure in South India

üî•Don't forget to Subscribe to follow our journey and see what we get up to next in Kochi!

description:

After a long drive to Pune, we received a warm welcome from our Indian family ‚Äî full of love, smiles, and chai ‚òïÔ∏è The best part? Exchanging gifts and reconnecting with everyone after months apart! ‚ù§Ô∏è This vlog marks the beginning of our Diwali adventures ‚Äî full of culture, colors, and family time. Don‚Äôt miss the emotional and fun start to our India journey! üáÆüá≥‚ú®

description:
Part 3 of 4 of my Europe trip! I stayed in Paris, solo, for 4 days. title: Visiting the Philippines Closest Island to Malaysia
description:
Just a few Kilometers off the coast of Malaysia is a Philippine Island home to sea gypsies travelling across the border to buy and sell their products.

This island boundary is strictly guarded and to get there it will take several days of travel.

On this trip, We went to the last island still under the control of the Philippines and here we were surprised by our discoveries.

Because the island is so remote, only a few are lucky enough to be able to show what is here on the island that is still part of the Philippines.

SUBSCRIBE FOR MORE ADVENTURE!

title: Inside America's City of Zombies | Largest Zombie Town in America | Kensington, Philadelphia
description:
Inside America's City of Zombies | Largest Zombie Town in America | Kensington, Philadelphia

‡¥µ‡¥ø‡¥¶‡µá‡¥∂‡¥∞‡¥æ‡¥ú‡µç‡¥Ø‡¥ô‡µç‡¥ô‡¥≥‡¥ø‡µΩ ‡¥â‡¥™‡¥∞‡¥ø‡¥™‡¥†‡¥®‡¥§‡µç‡¥§‡¥ø‡¥®‡µç ‡¥™‡µã‡¥ï‡µÅ‡¥µ‡¥æ‡µª ‡¥§‡¥æ‡¥≤‡µç‡¥™‡¥∞‡µç‡¥Ø‡¥Æ‡µÅ‡¥≥‡µç‡¥≥‡¥µ‡µº‡¥ï‡µç‡¥ï‡µç STUDYLINKS ‡¥®‡µÜ ‡¥¨‡¥®‡µç‡¥ß‡¥™‡µç‡¥™‡µÜ‡¥ü‡¥æ‡¥Ç.

In this vlog, I take you through one of the most shocking and heartbreaking experiences of my travels ‚Äî walking down the so-called ‚ÄúZombie Streets‚Äù of Philadelphia. What I witnessed here was unlike anything I‚Äôve ever seen before: people trapped in addiction, abandoned streets that look like something out of a horror movie, and the harsh reality of America‚Äôs dark side.

While Philadelphia is known for its rich history, culture, and food, there is another side that most tourists never see. This vlog shows the raw truth of urban struggles, homelessness, and drug addiction in one of the most developed countries in the world.

This is not meant to shame or sensationalize, but to shed light on a growing crisis that affects countless lives. Watching this will give you a glimpse of the unseen reality behind America‚Äôs glittering cities.

If you found this video eye-opening, make sure to like, share, and subscribe for more real travel experiences and behind-the-scenes stories from around the world.

title: Solo in Kenya‚Äôs Most Dangerous Slum üá∞üá™
description:
Nairobi, Kenya ‚ûñ I travel to one of the largest slums in Africa and one of the most densely populated places in the world. Kibera is home to an estimated million people living in small tin shacks, many without access to clean water or proper sanitation.

Located just a few kilometers from Nairobi‚Äôs city center, it feels like a completely different world. Yet despite the challenges, the community is alive with energy, street markets, and people trying to make the most of what little they have.

I'll walk through the deep alleys of Kibera, meet local residents, explore their homes, and see first hand what life is really like here.

title: Our Thailand Shopping & Return Journey ‚úàÔ∏è  | TRIP PISSO
description:
‚úç In this vlog, we explored Indra Square, Big C, and Indra Market for some amazing shopping in Bangkok. From souvenirs to trendy items, we grabbed some great deals ‚Äî and the highlight of the trip was buying a DJI drone! üöÅ‚ú®

title: Is Real Estate a Good Investment in 2025?
description:
My view is that buying and holding real estate is not an effective investment strategy in our current economic environment, for a few reasons.

1) Real estate is more interest rate sensitive than it is inflation sensitive, so given our current circumstances it is likely to go down in real terms

2) It is a fixed asset that is easy to tax, which limits its impacts on your ability to diversify

3) Real estate is nailed down, so investing in it makes it more difficult to move money from one place to another

That‚Äôs my view, in a nutshell. I‚Äôm curious to hear if you agree.

How does the stock market work? - Oliver Elfenbaum
description:

Check out our full book recommendation: https://shop.ed.ted.com/products/the-richest-man-in-babylon

--

In the 1600s, the Dutch East India Company employed hundreds of ships to trade goods around the globe. In order to fund their voyages, the company turned to private citizens to invest money to support trips in exchange for a share of the profits. In doing so, they unknowingly invented the world‚Äôs first stock market. So how do companies and investors use the market today? Oliver Elfenbaum explains.

THE SHOW:
Hasan Minhaj Doesn‚Äôt Know is a long-form interview podcast hosted by two-time Peabody Award-winning comedian Hasan Minhaj. The show features in-depth conversations with politicians and public figures, as well as occasional interviews with celebrities. title: Why $100K Should Be Your First Goal
description:
If you can make your first $100K, your next $100K is way easier.

If you invest $10,000 a year with a 7% return, it‚Äôll take around 7.84 years to reach your first $100K.

But thanks to compound interest, your second $100K will only take about 5.1 years to grow.

Crazy right? Your first $100K takes up 26% of the time it takes to become a millionaire ‚Äî and the remaining $900K only takes 74%.

So if you can hit $100K, you‚Äôre already 25% of the way to $1 million.

Choosing the right investment tools is essential for building wealth, and Fidelity offers some of the best options with its wide range of index funds. Among these, four standout options are tailored to different financial goals and investor profiles.

The Fidelity 500 Index Fund (FXAIX) tracks the S&P 500, offering exposure to large-cap U.S. companies across various industries. With a low expense ratio of just 0.015% and strong historical returns, this fund is a core holding for long-term investors seeking steady growth with relative stability.

The Fidelity Total Market Index Fund (FSKAX) provides exposure to the entire U.S. stock market, including large-, mid-, and small-cap companies. Its broad diversification makes it a comprehensive choice for those seeking a one-stop solution for their portfolio. While slightly more volatile due to smaller company exposure, its low expense ratio and historical returns make it an attractive option.

For international diversification, the Fidelity Total International Index Fund (FTIHX) focuses on markets outside the U.S., spanning developed and emerging economies. Although recent returns have lagged behind U.S. markets, the fund offers long-term potential and reduces reliance on domestic markets, making it a key addition for globally minded investors.

The Fidelity Freedom Index Funds are target-date funds designed for hands-off investors. These funds automatically adjust asset allocations over time, balancing growth and income preservation as retirement approaches. With low expense ratios and a diversified mix of asset classes, they simplify retirement planning for those seeking an easy, long-term solution.

These four Fidelity index funds cater to various investment strategies, from U.S.-focused growth to global diversification and hands-off retirement planning. Their low costs and potential for strong returns make them excellent options for building wealth over the long term.

title: Why You Should Invest Early
description:
‚ÄúThe 20s are for fun ü§© - I‚Äôll invest in my 30s anyways!‚Äù 

If that‚Äôs your mindset, read ahead üëáüèª

Were you surprised to see the 1st child have a higher net worth than the 2nd child at the end of the reel? üí∞

If you were wondering how it‚Äôs through the Power of COMPOUNDING üòé

For the first 10 years, boy no.1 chose to invest his INR 50,000 pocket money üíµ at an interest of 12%, earning him approximately INR 1.2 crores but then decided not to invest for the next 20 years. 

While the 2nd boy did the opposite and partied üï∫üèª for the first 10 years and seriously invested for the next 20 years, finally earning him INR 5 crores. 

‚û°Ô∏è Here‚Äôs why the 1st boy earned more money in the end, even though he invested a lesser portion of the money gifted to him.

The answer is TIME !! üï∞Ô∏è 

While the 2nd boy was busy partying, the investments made by the first boy kept compounding. By the time the 2nd boy started investing, the 1st boy‚Äôs investments were already worth INR 1.2 crores. üí∏

So no matter how long the 2nd boy keeps investing INR 50,000 monthly, the gap between them keeps growing even though the 1st boy stopped investing after the first 10 years. 

That‚Äôs how powerful compounding is üí™üèª No wonder Albert Einstein called compounding the 8th wonder of the world üëèüèª

‚ö†Ô∏è Having fun is nice, but keep a portion of your income to invest from day 1 of earning money üôåüèª

1Ô∏è‚É£ Save Emergency Funds: Before you even start, make sure you don save like 3-6 months of your living expenses for emergency. Anything fit happen, so you need backup. 

2Ô∏è‚É£ Treasury Bills: Put some money for Treasury Bills‚Äîsteady returns, low risk. E no go blow up your phone, but e go give you some peace of mind. üìäüìà

3Ô∏è‚É£ Gold & Precious Metals: Gold no dey lose value like that. If wahala burst for market, gold go still shine. Add small gold or other precious metals for your portfolio. üí∞‚ú®

4Ô∏è‚É£ Nigerian & US Stocks: E get some Nigerian and US stocks wey get better potential. Look into platforms like Yochaa and others. Diversify and spread your risk‚Äîno put all your eggs for one basket! ü•öüìâüìà

5Ô∏è‚É£ Keep Working Hard: Investing is good, but no forget say your hustle still matters. Keep working, keep earning, and keep topping up your investments! üëäüèæüíº

title: THE PSYCHOLOGY OF MONEY (BY MORGAN HOUSEL)
description:
Support the channel by getting The Psychology of Money by Morgan Housel here: https://amzn.to/3aTPV3a 

As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualified purchases.

---

Have you heard the story about Ronald Read, the janitor that had 8 million dollars in savings when he died in 2014? Yes, you heard that right. Janitor. $8 millions. And he didn¬¥t win the lottery or inherit the money either. He just saved consistently throughout his life, while letting the wonders of compounding do its thing. The morale is that your behaviour with money is oftentimes more important than how intelligent you are. Even if you don¬¥t have a diploma from Harvard, or work on Wall Street, you can become rich by just behaving in a sound way. As Morgan Housel puts it: ‚Äúfinancial success is not a hard science. It‚Äôs a soft skill, where how you behave is more important than what you know.‚Äù Spend your next ten or fifteen minutes on this video, and you might excel on the soft skill of investing! This is a top 5 takeaways summary of The Psychology of Money, by Morgan Housel.

---

Also, for my private stock portfolio & revealing insights into my investment strategy, head over to: https://www.patreon.com/TheSwedishInvestor 

---

Want to know more about human psychology and its relation to money? Check out my top 10 (!) takeaways from Thinking Fast and Slow by Daniel Kahneman here: https://youtu.be/cuj2Kq8rvGw 

---

Top 5 takeaway of The Psychology of Money by Morgan Housel:
00:00 Intro
01:14 1. Pay the Price
04:18 2. Never Enough
07:50 3. Crazy is in the Eye of the Beholder
10:32 4. Peek-A-Boo
12:30 5. The Seduction of Pessimism

---

My goal with this channel is to help you make more money and improve your personal finances. How to become a millionaire? There are many ways to get there ‚Äì investing in the stock market, becoming a stock trader, doing real estate investing, or why not becoming an entrepreneur? But whether you are interested in how to invest in stocks or investing strategies for creating passive income with rental properties ‚Äì I hope to be able to provide you with a solution (or at least an idea) here. Warren Buffett - the greatest investor of our time - says that you should fill your mind with competing ideas and then see what makes sense to you. This channel is about filling your mind with those ideas. And in the process ‚Äì upgrading your money-making toolbox.

title: The Millionaire Investing Advice For Teenagers
description:
For anyone who wanted a video about how to invest as a teenager, or what to do when you turn 18 years old - here is that video, enjoy! Add me on Instagram: GPStephan

Second Channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCa-ckhlKL98F8YXKQ-BALiw

The YouTube Creator Academy: 
Learn EXACTLY how to get your first 1000 subscribers on YouTube, rank videos on the front page of searches, grow your following, and turn that into another income source: https://bit.ly/2STxofv $100 OFF WITH CODE 100OFF 

Get 2 Free Stocks on WeBull when you deposit $100 (Valued up to $1000): https://act.webull.com/k/Vowbik9Tm5he/main

My ENTIRE Camera and Recording Equipment: 
https://www.amazon.com/shop/grahamstephan?listId=2TNWZ7RP1P1EB


FIRST: GET A CREDIT CARD
Doing this is VERY easy - as a first credit card, I highly recommend The Discover It Secured Card. 
All you need to do is put down a small deposit, and they will give you a credit card with a limit equal to that amount. To build your credit, all you need to do is put a minimal amount on the credit card each month, then pay it off in full to avoid paying any interest. It‚Äôs as simple as that, the entire process should take you less than 15 minutes to do.

SECOND: GET A BANK ACCOUNT
I think it‚Äôs incredibly important that you have a bank account that‚Äôs solely in your own name, that ONLY you have access to - this is just one step closer to becoming a productive, financially responsible adult. Again, this step is just about learning how to manage money on your own, and eventually becoming an independent adult who can support themselves financially‚Ä¶and smash the like button.

THIRD: GET A ROTH IRA
A Roth IRA is a tax advantaged retirement account that lets you contribute post tax money‚Ä¶meaning taxes have already been taking out of what you earned‚Ä¶and by the time you‚Äôre 59.5, all the PROFIT in that account can be accessed completely tax free. 

FOURTH: STAY OUT OF CONSUMER DEBT
 I‚Äôm not referring to a low interest rate mortgage on a rental property, or any type of leverage that makes you more money‚Ä¶instead, I‚Äôm referring to credit card debt, expensive personal loans, high interest auto loans, or ANY other type of loan that serves no purpose other than to make your life awful. The responsible way to handle purchases is to only buy things that you can afford, put it in a credit card‚Ä¶and then PAY THE CREDIT CARD OFF IN FULL before its due. 

FIFTH: GET A JOB
I sound like some old man saying this, but no joke, if there‚Äôs ANYTHING that set me up for a successful future, and that got me started on the right path early in life‚Ä¶it was this. GET A JOB. Anything. Even if it‚Äôs a few hours per week, JUST GET SOME WORK EXPERIENCE. Doesn‚Äôt matter how much money you make, just work‚Ä¶the experience that you‚Äôll get from a part time job will be worth it 100x over by the time you‚Äôre older.

SIXTH: LIVE BELOW YOUR MEANS
Do not buy stupid stuff to impress people who don‚Äôt matter. Do not waste your money on things that aren‚Äôt going to benefit you long term. I‚Äôm a firm believer that it‚Äôs totally okay and acceptable to live SUPER cheaply in your 20‚Äôs, to set up the rest of your life to live comfortably.

SEVENTH: DONT GO TO COLLEGE JUST TO GO TO COLLEGE
Here‚Äôs my solution: if you don‚Äôt know what you want to do with your life, either go and get work experience until you figure it out - or go to a 2-year community college part time while you work. This way, you can save a TON of money - you can continue working at the same time - and that gives you more time to figure out what you really want to do. 

EIGHTH: INVESTING ADVICE FOR TEENAGERS:
For most people out there, just invest in a broad low-cost index fund, invest consistently, and invest with the expectation of holding it for the next 30-40 years. That‚Äôs literally it. An index fund like FZROX, VTSAX, FIAX, or a target date retirement fund through Vanguard would do the trick. If you just do this one investment, chances are, this will become you full retirement when you‚Äôre older. 

Now, If you ARE going to take on more risk, while you‚Äôre young is the time to do it. If you want to start that business, DO IT. If you‚Äôre successful at it, then you‚Äôre further ahead financially. Either way, you win‚Ä¶even if you LOSE, it‚Äôs better you lose a small amount when you‚Äôre 18, then a LARGE amount when you‚Äôre 35.

So don‚Äôt let those mistakes be made in vain‚Ä¶if everyone can learn from what I did wrong, then at least my mistakes went to a good purpose.

For business or one-on-one real estate investing/real estate agent consulting inquiries, you can reach me at GrahamStephanBusiness@gmail.com

title: Ryan Davis: UNDER-RATED {FULL COMEDY SPECIAL} Presented by Ali Siddiq
description:
Ryan Davis returns with his latest stand-up special, Under-Rated ‚Äî his YouTube debut and a fearless, hilarious set exclusively on Ali Siddiq‚Äôs channel. From personal stories to cultural hot takes, Ryan delivers punchlines that hit hard and moments you won‚Äôt forget.

For years, Ryan Davis has built a massive following online with his sharp takes on culture, relationships, and everyday life. Now, he‚Äôs bringing that same energy to the stage with Under-Rated, a bold, unfiltered, laugh-out-loud funny special that cements his place as one of the most talked-about voices in comedy.

In this new special, Ryan dives into controversial cultural conversations, complicated family dynamics, gender double standards, and personal moments that are as shocking as they are hilarious. He blends raw honesty with quick wit, seamlessly moving between real-life stories and sharp social commentary, keeping the audience fully locked in from beginning to end.

This isn‚Äôt just another comedy set‚Äîit‚Äôs Ryan Davis making a statement on one of the biggest comedy platforms on YouTube. If you‚Äôve followed his viral clips for years, this is the moment you‚Äôve been waiting for. And if you‚Äôre new to Ryan Davis, get ready to see why audiences across the country can‚Äôt get enough of him.

üìå Subscribe to the channel for more exclusive specials, live shows, and legendary moments from today‚Äôs top comedians.

Check out tour dates: https://www.alisiddiq.com/

Connect on social media!
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/alisiddiq/?hl=en
Facebook: https://facebook.com/ali.siddiq.92
TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@thealisiddiq
Twitter: https://twitter.com/ali_speaks

Ali Siddiq is a stand-up comedian, public speaker, and writer out of Houston. Ali‚Äôs unique style of stand-up began behind the walls of incarceration, an incubator for interesting experiences and good stories.  
 
People received their first taste of Ali Siddiq when he appeared on HBO's DEF COMEDY JAM and LIVE FROM GOTHAM, and in 2013 he was named Comedy Central's "#1 Comic to Watch".  In 2014, Ali impressed comedy enthusiasts by displaying his ability to captivate an audience with his "Mexicans Got On Boots" tale, descriptive storytelling, with over 15 million views, of a prison riot on THIS IS NOT HAPPENING, the first of three appearances.  His stories continued with his HALF HOUR special, which premiered on Comedy Central in the fall of 2016.  Immediately following the premiere of that special, Comedy Central offered Ali an hour-special where he performed for inmates live in a Texas jail, sending Ali back to where it all started. The hour special, Ali Siddiq: It‚Äôs Bigger Than These Bars, premiered in February 2018 on Comedy Central.  In 2019, Ali could be seen as a Top 5 finalist on NBC‚Äôs BRING THE FUNNY. Most recently, Ali could be seen as a guest on THE JOE ROGAN EXPERIENCE.

Yash Soni is an Indian actor best known for his work in Gujarati cinema. Born on 16 October 1996 in Ahmedabad, he gained popularity with his debut film Chhello Divas (2015), a youth-based comedy that became a major hit. He later appeared in successful films like Shu Thayu?, Chaal Jeevi Laiye! one of the highest-grossing Gujarati movies, Naadi Dosh, Raado, and Fakt Mahilao Maate. Known for his natural acting style and strong screen presence, Yash Soni has become one of the leading faces of modern Gujarati cinema. He also acted in the Hindi remake Days of Tafree (2016).
